The paper introduces a novel technique for transferring biomarker information between related neurodegenerative diseases using a joint-disease generative model of biomarker progressions. This involves exploiting biomarker relationships that are shared across diseases. The paper also mentions the use of deep learning approaches, but emphasizes the interpretability of their proposed method. Given these factors, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The use of MRI scans and DTI scans also suggests the possibility of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-categories.
